description.description_en: Evergreen tree, usually 4-25 m high, with trunk to 5 m. in diam, the bark dark brown to black; banchlets stout; terminal buds with papyraceous scales.Leaves coriaceous, broadly ovate to lanceolate-elliptic or rarely elliptic, deep green, glossy, 5-10.5 cm long, 3-8 cm broad, rounded or broad obtuse at base, acuminate to cuspidate at apex, slighly thicker and undulate at margin, entire at the lower part, serrulate distally, pinnate-nerved; petiole 3-8 cm long.Inflorescece 6-10 cm long, 14- to 23-flowered, bract thin-papyraceous, linear, 1-2 cm long; pedicels 1-3 cm long, in fruit much longer; stamnes 40-75, spreading at first in protandrous tree and downard in protogynous tree, filaments erect when shedding pollen; carpels (5-)7-11, with 16-30 ovules.Follicetum 6-10 mm wide, with persistent dry stigma;seeds 5-12 per follicle, linear ellipsoid, 3-4 mm long.
